Column Comment.0: PROJECT IDENTIFIER: unique identifier for the project.
Column Comment.1: ACTIVE INDICATOR: A Y or N flag indicating whether this row of data is currentlyeither active/valid (Y) or inactive/invalid (N).
Column Comment.2: COMPLETION DATE: the date that the project was completed.
Column Comment.3: CONFIDENTIAL INDICATOR: a yes / no flag indicating whether the project isconfidential.
Column Comment.4: CONFIDENTIAL RELEASE DATE: the date that a confidential project will becomenon-confidential, so that information may be released.
Column Comment.6: EFFECTIVE DATE: The date that the data in this row first came into effect.
Column Comment.7: EXPIRY DATE: The date that the data in this row was no longer active or in effect.
Column Comment.8: FIELD STATION INDICATOR: a yes / no flag indicating that field stations were usedin the project.
Column Comment.9: LAND RIGHT INDICATOR: a yes / no flag indicating that a land right is involved inthe project.
Column Comment.10: PDEN INDICATOR: a yes / no flag indicating that a PDEN is involved in the project.
Column Comment.11: ROW_MANAGEMENT_GUID: This value may be used to provide a global uniqueidentifier for this row of data. Use of this column is not mandatory, but if used,optional PPDM NOT NULL and UNIQUE INDEX constraints provided in the datamodel DDL should be created.
Column Comment.12: PROJECT NAME: the name assigned to the project.
Column Comment.13: PROJECT NUMBER: a code or reference number assigned to the project by thesponsoring organization.
Column Comment.14: PROJECT TYPE: the type of project, such as seismic, geological, exploitation etc.
Column Comment.15: REMARK: Narrative remarks about this row of data.
Column Comment.16: SEISMIC SET INDICATOR: a yes / no flag indicating that one or more seismic setsare involved in the project.
Column Comment.17: SOURCE: The individual, company, state, or government agency designated as thesource of information for this row.
Column Comment.18: START DATE: the date that work on the project commenced.
Column Comment.19: STRAT COLUMN INDICATOR: a yes / no flag indicating that one or morestratigraphic columns are involved in the project.
Column Comment.20: STRATIGRAPHIC INTERPRETATION INDICATOR: a yes / no flag indicating thatone or more stratigraphic interpretations are involved in the project. May include wellpicks or field station interpretations.
Column Comment.21: WELL INDICATOR: a yes / no flag indicating that one or more wells is involved in theproject.
Column Comment.22: ROW CHANGED BY: Application login id of the user who last changed the row.
Column Comment.23: ROW CHANGED DATE: System date of the last time the row was changed.
Column Comment.24: ROW CREATED BY: System user who created this row of data.
Column Comment.25: ROW CREATED DATE: Date that the row was created on.
Column Comment.26: ROW_EFFECTIVE_DATE: A system assigned date that specified when a row of datais effective from a systems perspective. This may be the date that a row of data wasmade available to end users, for example.
Column Comment.27: ROW_EXPIRY_DATE: A system assigned date that specified when a row of data isno longer effective from a systems perspective. This may be the date that a row ofdata was no longer available to end users, for example.
Column Comment.28: PPDM ROW QUALITY: A set of values indicating the quality of data in this row,usually with reference to the method or procedures used to load the data, althoughother types of quality reference are permitted.
